The paper deals with clustering uncertain data, which is a common problem in databases and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm that utilizes consistency among possible worlds, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which is a common theme in social and information sciences (cs.SI).
